cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the use of Non-Orthogonal Multiple Access (NOMA) and caching to increase the capacity of future 5G wireless systems. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, given the focus on wireless communication and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses power allocation strategies, which further supports the likelihood of cs.IT being the primary sub-category.
